radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is seen in the right lower quadrant, dilated to a 9 mm with hyperenhancement and minimal adjacent stranding. Tiny hypodensities within the right hepatic lobe are likely cysts or biliary hamartomas. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, bilateral adrenal glands, kidneys, small and large bowel are normal. No free fluid or lymphadenopathy is identified.
